 in controlling who can invite or join you in games. To stop auto joining friends, you should tweak these settings:\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Log in to your Roblox account.<\/li>\n  <li>Click on the gear icon located at the upper-right corner to access Settings.<\/li>\n  <li>Navigate to the “Privacy” tab.<\/li>\n  <li>Locate the option labeled “Who can join me in a game?”<\/li>\n  <li>Change this setting from “Friends” or “Everyone” to “No one” or “Friends of Friends” depending on your preference.<\/li>\n  <li>Save your changes.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\nBy restricting who can join your game, you reduce the chances of being automatically pulled into a friend’s session.\n\n<h3>2. Manage Game Invitations and Notifications<\/h3>\n\nSometimes, auto joining happens because you accept or don’t notice game invitations. To minimize this:\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Turn off or mute game invite notifications to avoid accidental acceptance.<\/li>\n  <li>Be cautious about clicking “Join” on notifications or game invites.<\/li>\n  <li>If you use the Roblox mobile app, check notification settings both within the app and on your device.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\nManaging invitations helps you stay in control of when and where you join games.\n\n<h3>3. Use the “Leave Game” Button Effectively<\/h3>\n\nIf you find yourself auto joined into a friend’s game, don’t hesitate to use the “Leave Game” option immediately. This can be a quick way to exit an unwanted session without much hassle.\n\n<h2>Understanding Party and Group Settings<\/h2>\n\nRoblox groups and parties also influence how players join games together. If you’re part of a group or party, you might experience auto joining more frequently.\n\n<h3>Controlling Party Invites<\/h3>\n\nParties allow friends to join and play games simultaneously, but you can control party invites:\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Open the Roblox party chat window.<\/li>\n  <li>Access party settings and adjust who can invite you.<\/li>\n  <li>Set it to “Friends” or “No one” if you want fewer interruptions.<